        <num>CC 3291</num>
        <heading>3291.  Presumption that things are subject to conventional mortgage</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3291.  Presumption that things are subject to conventional mortgage
A conventional mortgage of a corporeal immovable, servitude of right of use, or lease, as the case may be, includes the things made susceptible of mortgage with them by Article 3286, unless the parties expressly agree to the contrary.</p>
        </content>
